cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with content caching in a network, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The optimization problem formulation and solution involve linear programming (cs.DS) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses numerical experiments and caching gain, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG).
